================================================================================
THIRD-PARTY RUNTIME DEPENDENCIES
================================================================================

stavR depends on the following third-party Node packages at runtime. Each is
distributed under its own license; the canonical license text travels with the
package itself in node_modules/<pkg>/LICENSE. License identifiers below use
SPDX shortcodes.

Model Context Protocol SDK
--------------------------
@modelcontextprotocol/sdk (MIT) — official TypeScript SDK for MCP servers and
clients. Used by the daemon HTTP / stdio transports and by the worker-spawner
adapter (v0.7 PR alpha) to invoke worker MCP child processes.
https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/typescript-sdk

WebAuthn server library
-----------------------
@simplewebauthn/server (MIT) — added in v0.7 Phase 1. Validates registration
attestations and authentication assertions against the operator's passkey.
Authors: Matthew Miller and contributors.
https://github.com/MasterKale/SimpleWebAuthn

mDNS service discovery
----------------------
bonjour-service (MIT) — added in v0.7 Phase 2. Advertises this daemon as
_stavr._tcp.local on the LAN and discovers other stavR instances for the
federation peer registry. Active maintained fork of the original `bonjour`
package by ON LX Ltd. and contributors.
https://github.com/onlxltd/bonjour-service

Database and persistence
------------------------
better-sqlite3 (MIT) — synchronous SQLite bindings backing runestone.db.
yaml (ISC) — YAML parser used for peers.yaml + worker-mcp-servers.yaml +
            operator-supplied policy presets.

HTTP and observability
----------------------
express (MIT) — HTTP server framework for the dashboard + /api/* routes.
zod (MIT) — schema validation across the broker event surface and BOM types.
@opentelemetry/sdk-node (Apache-2.0) — OpenTelemetry SDK used for tracing.
pino (MIT) — structured logger used in production mode.

Each runtime dependency contributes its own LICENSE file under node_modules.
No code is statically vendored from these packages; they are consumed as
declared dependencies in package.json and resolved at npm install time.

================================================================================
v0.7 FAMILY-SCALE INFRASTRUCTURE
================================================================================

The v0.7 federation layer (peers.yaml + mDNS + WebAuthn passkeys) was designed
in conversation with Cowork-Claude during the 2026-05-18/19 session that
produced ADR-042. Five interlocking decisions (federation roles, peer
discovery, operator identity, instruction-flow visualization, worker
polymorphism) were brainstormed via the 10-3-1 ideation rule and locked in
ADR-042 with cross-references to ADR-034 §B (family-scale positioning).

stavR's WebAuthn use is conventional — passkey as the operator's root
identity, with Tier 3 EXPLICIT actions gated on a fresh assertion. The
FIDO Alliance and W3C are credited as authors of the underlying specs.
